"========== Content ==========
<h3>Is Incalculability a Defense for Ignorance?</h3>

<p>We talk a good deal about pragmatism.  It's as if being pragmatic sidesteps more difficult issues that require time and cerebral resources to sort.  Time and cerebral resources we hope to apply to something else, something of more immediate resolve.  Some might say, "Don't worry about the theoretical underpinnings of your choices; don't try to be right.  Just try to be right enough, right now."</p>
